#### [NEW] [dim_season.sql](file:///c:/Satva/Tech/ETL_F1/f1-pipeline/warehouse/dbt/models/marts/dimensions/dim_season.sql)

**Grain**: 1 row per F1 season (~76 rows)
**Materialization**: `table`
**Source**: `int_race_bridge` + `int_standings_driver_eoy` + `int_standings_constructor_eoy` + `int_driver_bridge`

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `season_year` | SMALLINT | PK — season year |
| `total_races` | INT | Races in the season |
| `driver_champion_name` | VARCHAR | WDC winner name — **NULL if season in progress** |
| `constructor_champion_name` | VARCHAR | WCC winner name — **NULL if season in progress** |
| `champion_points` | DECIMAL | Champion's total points |
| `champion_wins` | INT | Champion's wins that year |
| `era_label` | VARCHAR | e.g., "Front-engine", "Ground Effect", "V10", "Turbo Hybrid" |
| `dw_created_at` | TIMESTAMP | Record creation time |

**Mid-season / incomplete season rule**: Champion columns are derived by looking up the driver at `championship_position = 1` in `int_standings_driver_eoy`. If that position doesn't exist (season not yet complete), all champion columns resolve to `NULL`. Do **not** default to a placeholder — NULL is the correct, honest value. The dashboard layer handles this with a "Season in progress" label.

**`era_label` mapping logic**:
```
1950-1957: "Front-engine"
1958-1965: "Rear-engine Revolution"
1966-1976: "3-Litre Era"
1977-1982: "Ground Effect"
1983-1988: "Turbo Era"
1989-1994: "Naturally Aspirated"
1995-2005: "V10 Era"
2006-2013: "V8 Era"
2014-2024: "Turbo Hybrid V6"
2025+:     "2026 Regulations"
```

