#### [NEW] [fct_race_result.sql](file:///c:/Satva/Tech/ETL_F1/f1-pipeline/warehouse/dbt/models/marts/facts/fct_race_result.sql)

**Grain**: 1 row per driver × race start (~28K rows)
**Materialization**: `incremental` — unique_key = `result_id`, strategy = `merge`
**Source**: `int_results_enriched`

**Required dbt config block**:
```sql
{{
  config(
    materialized         = 'incremental',
    unique_key           = 'result_id',
    incremental_strategy = 'merge'
  )
}}
```

> [!NOTE]
> MERGE strategy handles corrections. If a Jolpica result row is retroactively corrected (e.g., DSQ after the race), the MERGE will overwrite the stale row using `result_id` as the match key. New seasons append; corrections update in-place.

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `result_id` | INT | PK — from `int_results_enriched` |
| `race_key` | INT | FK → `dim_race` |
| `driver_key` | INT | FK → `dim_driver` |
| `constructor_key` | INT | FK → `dim_constructor` |
| `circuit_key` | INT | FK → `dim_circuit` |
| `season_year` | SMALLINT | Partition column |
| `round_number` | TINYINT | Round within season |
| `grid_position` | TINYINT | Starting grid position |
| `finish_position` | TINYINT | Finishing position (NULL = DNF) |
| `finish_position_text` | VARCHAR | Position text (includes "R", "D", etc.) |
| `points_scored` | DECIMAL(5,2) | Championship points earned |
| `laps_completed` | INT | Laps completed |
| `race_time_ms` | BIGINT | Race time in ms (winner only) |
| `fastest_lap_rank` | TINYINT | Rank of fastest lap |
| `fastest_lap_speed_kph` | DECIMAL(6,3) | Fastest lap speed |
| `race_status` | VARCHAR | Resolved status text |
| `qualifying_position` | TINYINT | Grid position from qualifying |
| `positions_gained` | SMALLINT | `grid_position - finish_position` |
| `is_winner` | BOOLEAN | `finish_position = 1` |
| `is_podium` | BOOLEAN | `finish_position <= 3` |
| `is_points_finish` | BOOLEAN | `points_scored > 0` |
| `is_pole` | BOOLEAN | `qualifying_position = 1` |
| `is_fastest_lap` | BOOLEAN | `fastest_lap_rank = 1` |
| `is_dnf` | BOOLEAN | Did not finish |
| `source_system` | VARCHAR | `kaggle` or `jolpica` |
| `dw_inserted_at` | TIMESTAMP | Record insert time |

**SQL approach**: Essentially a `SELECT *` from `int_results_enriched` with `positions_gained` and `is_points_finish` derived. The enriched model already has all the joins done.

