#### [NEW] [fct_lap_time.sql](file:///c:/Satva/Tech/ETL_F1/f1-pipeline/warehouse/dbt/models/marts/facts/fct_lap_time.sql)

**Grain**: 1 row per driver × lap (~550K+ rows from Kaggle, growing)
**Materialization**: `incremental` — unique_key = `['race_id', 'driver_id', 'lap_number']`
**Source**: `stg_kaggle_lap_times` (Kaggle 1996–2024) + `stg_openf1_laps` (OpenF1 2023+, has sector times)

> [!WARNING]
> This is the **largest table** in the warehouse. **Must** use incremental + partitioning or rebuild cost grows unbounded.

**Required dbt config block**:
```sql
{{
  config(
    materialized = 'incremental',
    unique_key   = ['race_id', 'driver_id', 'lap_number'],
    incremental_strategy = 'merge',
    partition_by = {'field': 'season_year', 'data_type': 'int'},
    cluster_by   = ['race_key']
  )
}}
```
Dashboard queries should **never** hit this directly — use mart tables instead.

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `race_key` | INT | FK → `dim_race` |
| `driver_key` | INT | FK → `dim_driver` |
| `season_year` | SMALLINT | Partition column |
| `lap_number` | INT | Lap number |
| `position_on_lap` | TINYINT | Position at end of lap |
| `lap_time_ms` | BIGINT | Lap time in milliseconds |
| `sector_1_ms` | BIGINT | Sector 1 time (OpenF1 only, NULL for Kaggle) |
| `sector_2_ms` | BIGINT | Sector 2 time (OpenF1 only) |
| `sector_3_ms` | BIGINT | Sector 3 time (OpenF1 only) |
| `is_pit_out_lap` | BOOLEAN | Pit out lap flag (OpenF1 only) |
| `source_system` | VARCHAR | `kaggle` or `openf1` |
| `dw_inserted_at` | TIMESTAMP | Record insert time |

**SQL approach**: UNION of Kaggle lap times (joined to races for year) and OpenF1 laps (joined through `int_driver_bridge` for `driver_id` resolution). OpenF1 laps that overlap with Kaggle laps for 2023-2024 will be deduplicated by preferring OpenF1 data (has sector times).

